De Beers Botswana Coal Mine Gets $260 Million Loan for Expansion

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-03-14T10:11:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/de-beers-botswana-coal-mine-gets-260-million-loan-for-expansion.html
Morupule Colliery Ltd., owned by  De
Beers  and the Botswana government, secured 1.7 billion pula
($260 million) in bank and shareholder loans to expand output at
its  coal mine  northeast of the capital Gaborone.  The Morupule mine will expand output to 3.2 million metric
tons a year from 1 million tons to feed state power plants, with
1.2 billion pula of the financing coming from bank borrowings
and 506 million pula from a shareholder loan, the Botswana
company said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
